         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Ivanhoe Cottage ¶ Robert St. Brisbane ¶ Sept 22nd /77 ¶ Baron von Mueller ¶ My dear Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.09.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M5, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dendrobium lichenastrum</seg> (MEL 544731).</p>
               </note>Ivanhoe Cottage</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Robert St. Brisbane</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sept 22nd /77</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose in this a very small Orchid which I found on the top of a high tree which was thrown by the road party on the top of Range Trinity Bay I send all the plants I could find to Bowen Park<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Queensland Acclimatisation Society's ground in Brisbane.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> where they are now in flower From the Flora<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham (1863-78)</seg>
                     <seg style="">, vol. 6, p. 287.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I think it may be <name key="Bolbophyllum%20lichenastrum">Bolbophyllum lichenastrum</name>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">F.M.</hi>
               </seg> a plant I have never come across — and perhaps you described that from a dried specimen and would therefore like to see a fresh plant I make the following notes on the veining &amp; colour as they are perhaps lost in drying</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plant forms irregular patches similar to <name key="Dendrobium%20linguefora">Dendrobium linguefora</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Dendrobium linguiforme?</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> for which I at first took it Sepals &amp; petals cream colour Lateral sepals marked with (5) five blood red veins, dorsal sepal having only (3) three blood red veins and the petals only one (1.) <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">central vein</hi>
               </seg> The labellum is a rich orange colour and marked with two (2) forked veins —</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for your kind enquiries after my health As the weather warms I find myself getting stronger</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever your much</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>obliged</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>F. M. Bailey</p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bolbophyllum%20lichenastrum">Bolbophyllum lichenastrum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dendrobium%20linguefora">Dendrobium linguefora</name>
            </p>
         </div>
